title: For Sale:  WTS Complete 5.45x39 AR upper half w/ Ballistic Advantage 8.3" barrel for pistol or SBR
postcontent:
5.45 upper. ALSO INCLUDES: 2 extra accessory rail sections for the hand guard, 1 modd'd P Mag to allow the follower to tilt a little, 

Built a 5.45 upper, bought 3 crates of surplus ammo. Before all my ammo arrived the ATF bans 7n6.  Took it to the range a couple times & shot up half of a tin (540 rd). Sure I ran it a little hard those days, but I let it cool between magazines, and its a melanite bore heavy profile barrel and the bore is bright and perfect. Ejection was good strong and consistent at 3:30.. I have a short vid of me doing a mag dump, it ran really great. 

Because of the corrosive primers, both times I cleaned the everloving hell out of it in the kitchen sink w/ soapy water, then dried it at 170f in the oven for a few minutes, the oiled it w/ oil base lube (rem oil), so it is in excellent condition. 

With the 7n6 ammo suddenly more costly to replace, and demanding cleaning regimen, I decided that having this extra chambering and upper was just not for me. I've sold the SF stock. I sold the five and half tins of the original six I had ordered. http://www.ar15.com/forums/t_7_133/1409135_WTS_76N_5_45_surplus_ammo_F2F_in_FL__GA_or_SC.html 

upper and charging handle are standard. HG is and a Middy JP FF Tube. I rounded off the back of the front sight rail so that it won't chafe the thumb. I will include a couple extra accessory rail sections. 

Barrel: Ballistic advantage 8.3" melanite/QPQ coated inside and out, new for $140 currently: 
http://ballisticadvantage.com/8-3-inch-545-spr-pistol-performance-barrel.html 

KAK slim flash can ($35) on there that protrudes past the HG. The HG is actually longer than the barrel so you would not be able to use a typical flash hider comp or brake on there w/o shortening/replacing the hand guard. 

BCG: Ballistic advantage phosphate coated, shot peened HP/MPI: bought it for $75. Carrier is a BCM M16 carrier. 

Gas Block: .750 BRT Pinnable low pro ($40). I got and drilled/pinned it myself so I'd never have to worry about locktite failing w/ hard use. This makes the barrel and gas block fitted parts, another gas block could be used if it a clamp on type of course, but this upper really works great and you wouldn't run a suppressor on this upper so I see no reason to ever replace it: 
http://www.blackrivertactical.com/concrete5/micropin-gas-block/ 

I travel around by car for my job alot all over SC, GA, FL. I can fly w/ it too no prob. Flying to NC & VA next week... 

If course, if you own AR15s, for you to leagally own this upper requires that at least one of your AR lowers is a SBR or pistol, or new stripped. 

w/ a $100 handguard, basic CH, gas tube, $50 upper & $50 carier, it would still cost over $500 easy to build, plust the effort. 

I'll also sell some of those HK416 mags if interested... 

Possibly interested in a trade for 22 LR barrel or upper. I alreay have a CMG Ciener type rimfire bolt but find accuracy through 5.56 barrels too poor.

title: For Sale:  HK USP 45 Tactical in .45 ACP Night Sights 704501TLE-A5
postcontent:
Enhanced versions of the USP, the USP Tactical models are designed for users who need the features found on the HK Mark 23, but in a more compact pistol. Both pistols approach the precision found on the Mark 23 by adding an extended threaded barrel with a rubber O-ring, adjustable trigger, and adjustable target-type sights.
Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.
All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.
The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.
Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.
The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.
 HK USP 45 Tactical in .45 ACP Night Sights link to deguns.net

Little more info about this underfolder. 

The Century AKMS is a U.S. made AK assembled from U.S. parts and a Polish military PMKMS under-folder parts set.  With a swap of the pistol grip it can be a near exact copy of a AKMS which is the folding stock variant of the AKM.

These rifles are use a Nodak Spud receiver with the correct dimples, unlike Century Arms' cheaper Romanian under-folders.  The quality is very high and the folding stock locks up very tightly.

Receiver - Stamped with correct magazine guide dimples and lightening cuts.  The receiver is US Made by Nodak Spud.

Butt Stock - Under folding stamped steel stock with correct dimples, rivets.   The stock is functional and not pinned open.

Pistol Grip - Black Composite.  This U.S. made grip can be replaced with a red or plum composite U.S. made grip to match the color on the military PMKMS.

Hand Guards - Laminated wood with correct palm swells.

Barrel - Chrome lined with bayonet lug and slant compensator.

Magazines - Takes any standard AK magazine.

Clone By - Century Internal Arms  Delray Beach, FL.

Description From Trijicon:

The TA31RCO is an Advanced Combat Optical Gunsight (ACOG) designed for the M4 and M4A1 weapon system. It incorporates dual illumination technology using a combination of fiber optics and self-luminous tritium. This allows the aiming point to always be illuminated without the use of batteries. The tritium illuminates the aiming point in total darkness, and the fiber optic self-adjusts reticle brightness during daylight according to ambient light conditions. This allows the operator to keep both eyes open while engaging targets and maintaining maximum situational awareness.

Designed to the exact specifications of the United States Marine Corps, the unique reticle pattern provides quick target acquisition at close combat ranges while providing enhanced target identification and hit probability out to 800 meters utilizing the Bullet Drop Compensator.

No tools are needed for windage and elevation adjustments because the TA31RCO features external adjusters, making it waterproof up to 11m without the caps. Mounting bosses are integrated into the housing by the eyepiece to allow the easy addition of a Trijicon RMR® (not included).
